input: ``Kruse was having an incredibly difficult time simply trying to dress himself. I'd have some word in my mind, but I couldn't figure out how to bring it to my lips. So Scott and Neal had to get me dressed and make sure my harness was on correctly, then Scott lowered me down the fixed ropes.`` By the time **Kruse** arrived in Base Camp, he says, ''it was still another three or four days before I could walk from my tent to the mess tent without stumbling all over the place.``''

input: Noble ``Thin Man'' Watts (February 17, 1926 -- August 28, 2004) was an American blues, jump blues and rhythm and blues saxophonist. He primarily played tenor saxophone.
